the ability to flourish,

ft. @broke_boutique 

anchored in riches gained  through trial and fear, 

our treasures keep us from the heavens, while saving us from the hell we may endure

all for us to try and find meaning in what’s next that this world may bring
——

as we look forward to working with broke boutique again in the future, it allows me to take a moment and appreciate how far Eugnell has come. 

With the tools I utilize with ai, it makes this process so much more fun, customizable, yet also challenges me to push myself to experiment in order to tell a more personable story.

This continues to make every session unique in its own way from start to finish 🙌🏾

just like Ashley, I’m thankful for all of my customers, followers, models, supporters, and everyone that allows us to do this for yet another year!!☺️

Lilith #1
ft. @silverbeauty.jennifer 

the common bridge between angels and demons is their ability to influence

but we are left with the ultimate power of free will

to live by a rule or to defy it lies in the hands of those that question it 

are we to be equal, to thrive, or to suffer
————-

Our freedom is in our ability to decide

to hone in on each moment 
and question what is our next act

we are damned for our curiosity and growth but praised for our obedience in a stagnant life

our freedom as we see is ours to choose

———-

Los Angeles once again showed me growth by helping me overcome my own trauma. 

My last trip to LA was pretty rough and had long lasting effects I didn’t expect.
But I strive for growth and I took those failures as opportunities to understand more of myself and what would be needed to try again.

I prepared and plan for what was needed and it truly made a difference. Thank you Los Angeles and everyone that was apart of it 🌹🌹🌹

More to come 
——

as the world catches fire
demons no longer hidden under shadows, 
we are met with moments thought only to fear in nightmares 

learning from whats revealed in the light, 
strength is earned from the weakness you overcome 

into the eyes, the truth of the demon lies 
the figure in our nightmares, 
a memory
a moment
a change 
a period in time in which we are tormented to witness the demon again 
.Without strength, without truth
she will will rage until the darkness over you is consumed

————-
 I was officially diagnosed with PTSD,
In a way I knew, but hearing it felt as if I was reliving the nightmares for the first time again and again 

adapting to a new world where you are free can feel like walking into a new realm of hell with all of the demons exposed for you now to see

light through the meadow 

I’ve been studying color theory more.
with my presentation in New Jersey, 
it’s where I felt my weakest area was in my knowledge 

It’s been fun diving back into the color wheel more and understanding why certain color palettes have appealed to me for so long

This session was my first shooting outside in this style with my normal lighting 
we did this pretty late but Evette always impresses me with the stylizing and wardrobe they can create on the fly

I could throw out a story I want to say, a color I want to represent, and bam, they have like 3 options  available :) 

I went primarily for complimentary colors here with the green grass and red fabric
Since she was wearing more pearlescent and white tones, I used a yellow gel on my strobe on the right to allow the colors to show I love! In editing I tried to bring out the purple more in the skirt. 

Overall I loved working outside of the studio with the new textures and colors, especially right after all my sessions in NYC. It was a nice way to end the trip 💚

Would love to hear everyone’s thoughts on this one.
